Update
September 9, 2020

We regret to inform you that a faculty member and 2 students that participate in extra curricular activities have tested positive for Covid-19. The students, faculty, and staff that were in close contact with these individuals have been notified and mandated to quarantine at home for 14 days. We are following CDC guidelines, protocols set by the State Department of Health and our school district, to decrease potential spread.

Should you have questions or concerns, please don't hesitate to contact our school office at (918) 652-6571.

Kelly Furer
High School Principal

post_text:
GREAT NEWS FREE MEALS!!!

Starting Sept 1 2020 EVERYONE in our district can eat for free! We are eligible for a different program and it will run through at least November.
So PLEASE participate in our meal program you may choose to pick up at the elementary from 10 to 11:30 or get meals delivered at 1 of our many stops. Please remember only 1 meal bag per child each day. If you could order your meal on our website it would really help in planning each day.
www.henryetta.k12.ok.us under the cafeteria tab
Even though ALL students are currently eligible for free meals we still need families to fill out a lunch application, our school uses this information for funding other than just the lunch program.
If you have ANY questions or need help locating a stop close to you please reach out. Bmcgowin@henryetta.k12.ok.us
918-652-6571 EXT 7763

think there has been some miscommunication.

Henryetta Athletics
August 25 at 11:45 AM ·

Attention H-Town:
We have decided to have a Senior Night Ceremony for the following FALL activities this Friday Night at 6:20 before our HOME Football Opener vs Okemah. Sr's and parents in Football, Softball, Band, Choir, Cheer, and Cross Country are asked to be at field by 6:05. Your students coach or director will help direct you to where to lineup. This will look at little different than the normal Sr Night. We want to be sure to give our Sr's and families an opportunity to be recognized and take pics sooner rather than later given the day to day uncertainty of activities. We will still plan another traditional ceremony for the last Home Game of season in November.

Be watching in the coming days for more info on GameDay and Facilities Procedures and Protocols for our Home Football games this Fall!!
#UKNIGHTED20/21

Henryetta Public Schools
August 21 at 9:43 AM ·

HPS - BREAKFAST/LUNCH ORDERS

We will be offering meal service to all students enrolled in HPS. PLEASE FILL OUT BY 10:00 P.M. DAILY for next day delivery (meals will be delivered Monday thru Friday). Example..Monday's meal will need to be ordered by 10:00 p.m. Sunday night
Please fill out survey once for each student. Each bag will contain 1 breakfast and 1 lunch.
Lunches will be available on 2 bus routes, North and South. Route details are on school website. Pick-up will be at the Elementary east door under the awning. Bus routes and pick-up will begin at 10:00 a.m. daily.
Please remember that meals will be charged according to pay status (free, reduced and paid).
If you have questions or need a lunch application, please call or email Bertha 918-652-6571 ext. 7763 or bmcgowin@henryetta.k12.ok.us
Thank you for participating and we look forward to serving you.

GO TO THE SCHOOL WEB PAGE TO PLACE ALL ORDERS
https://www.henryetta.k12.ok.us/2211_1

Should you have any questions or concerns, please don't hesitate to contact our school office at (918) 652-6571.

We will be offering meal service to all students ENROLLED in HPS. We are working on an order form for meals to help us be prepared. . We will be running 2 bus routes , north and south. Meals will also be available for pick-up from the elementary school from 10 to 11:30 a.m. Students or guardians will need to be able to provide students grade and name to receive a meal. Students may only receive 1 meal bag per student per day. Meal bags will contain 1 breakfast and 1 lunch.
Please remember that meals will be charged according to pay status (free, reduced and paid) So please remember to fill out a lunch application. These are available at all school buildings or you may print them from our website
We encourage everyone to participate and look forward to serving our students.

post_text:
Henryetta HS 10th Grade (Class of 2022) - information regarding Oklahoma's Promise

OKPromise has a new marketing page. Please share the following link with your parents and students: https://myokpromise.org/

If your student was in the 10th grade during the 2019-20 school year and you anticipate that your 2020 income may be under the $55,000 application limit for the Oklahoma’s Promise scholarship due to recent reductions in your income, you may submit an application based on your 2020 estimated income.

The application must be submitted prior to the June 30, 2020 deadline at https://secure.okcollegestart.org/applications/Oklahoma_Promise/apply.html. You will be required to provide a copy of your 2020 federal tax return when completed to verify that your 2020 income was under $55,000. The application will be held as pending until the tax documentation is received. Please send any questions to okpromise@osrhe.edu.

shared_text:
Green Country Technology Center is sharing a COVID-19 Update.
May 13 at 1:39 PM ·

We are nearing the end of Phase I of the GCTC COVID-19 Mitigation Plan and will be entering Phase II on Monday, May 18. Our current full-time students are finishing up their course work via distance learning this week and those completers will soon receive their grades and certificates.

Our mitigation plan was developed based on CDC suggested guidelines for reopening public places with input from the Oklahoma State Department of Career and Technology Education. Throughout Phase II our facility will continue to be closed to the public, however, our staff is onsite Mondays through Thursdays 8:00 am – 3:00 pm and Fridays 8:00 am – 12:00 pm. Our entire GCTC COVID-19 MITIGATION PLAN can be read at our website:
https://www.gctcok.edu/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1682277&type=d&pREC_ID=1862751

We thank you for your support during this time. Our focus will continue to be upon the health and welfare of our students, employees and stakeholders.

Henryetta Athletics
May 7 at 6:30 PM ·

Fishing Team Seniors!!
Quentin Story
Parents- Steve and Tammy Story

H.S.Activities- 3 band 4 years, basketball 4 years, fishing team 4 years, nhs 2 years

Future Plans- I plan on going to OSUIT and getting my basics in ecology and start fish college and pro bass fishing tournaments

Thoughts on Pandemic cutting Sr season short- "This has really been a bad deal for me because I had made some great friends this year in fishing and in the general high school and it is killing me to know that I will never get to step on our new gym floor and play with the team one last time or wake up at 3 in the morning to see if my fishing partner and I are as good as we think we are. Or play the fight song with the band one last time. I have loved every minute of high school and no one can take away the memories my friends/family and I have made together. I know this is a weird situation for all of us but if there is one thing that I know about my fellow Henryetta high schoolers is that everyone will find a way to make the best of this."
#CongratsQ
#Htownproud
#SrKnightMay8th8pm

#CongratsBaileyandKeaton
#Htownproud
#SrKnightMay8th8pm

(1) Bailey Ann Davis, Tennis (2) Jeremy and Tara Davis (3) Band 4 years, Drum Major 2 years, basketball 3 years, tennis 4 years, Regional runner up freshman year, Regionals 4th place junior year, Tennis state qualifier two years, National Honor Society 2 years, and Oklahoma Honor Society 2 years (4) I plan on going to Tulsa Community College and receiving a degree in Radiology/Sonography and becoming a Ultrasound Technician (5) I think COVID-19 was a shock for everyone, and no one was prepared for it and no one suspected it could effect and change our lives so suddenly. I know me and my tennis team had big hopes and ambitions that this season was going to be a great one, for both the boys and girls. I'm sad it was over so soon, but I'm very grateful for the memories I got to make with my team and coach.

Henryetta High School and Middle School Students:

Ms. Craig needs your help with getting some photos for the yearbook. Please email them to her at scraig@henryetta.k12.ok.us if you have any:

• Pictures of students in their prom attire (completely dressed up or not)
• Seniors – in caps/gowns (their choice of where they take the pictures) – we will also have pictures from traditional/virtual graduation we can use
• Seniors who would like to: write a letter to the coronavirus (Covid-19) about how it has affected your senior year
• Seniors – one baby picture
• HS and MS students – quarantine photos – photos that show what you have been doing to keep you busy and safe
• HS and MS spring sports athletes – ALL pictures welcome (even from a different year if you weren’t able to participate); also, if you want to, you may dress in your uniform (if you have it) and take a photo and submit.
Thank you.

shared_text:
Oklahoma State Department of Education
March 26 at 2:22 PM ·

Exciting news! 🎉 We have partnered with OETA to provide in-home learning opportunities for students. The goal is to bring parents, students and teachers together with content and curriculum to meet educational needs while schools are closed due to coronavirus.

Beginning Monday, March 30, OETA will be adjusting its daytime schedule to provide curriculum-based programming for students over the air on its broadcast channel, OETA WORLD. Programs will include PBS favorites like NOVA, Nature, American Experience and PBS KIDS programming.

Programming changes to OETA WORLD will take place Monday through Friday from 6 a.m. until 6 p.m. until the end of the school year.

Teachers and parents are encouraged to visit OETA.tv/LearningAtHome to view an updated program schedule, OETA’s statewide channel list, curriculum and activities.

post_text:
Parents, Guardians, and Students of Henryetta Public Schools:

Today HPS administration had a teleconference with the Okla. State Dept of Education. The recommendation is that we only have essential employees at the facilities during the school closure. Since this limits our staffing, HPS will offer a drive through grab and go lunch option behind the High School Cafeteria. You will drive in from the west and exit by the tennis courts. Remain in your car and take meals for each of your children 1-18 years old. We will serve lunches between 10-11:00 AM, M-F March 23rd- April 3rd. Food delivery via bus routes will not take place. Thank you for your patience and understanding as we are navigating through uncharted territory.

CORONAVIRUS UPDATE:

Parents, Guardians, and Students of Henryetta Public Schools:

Following Spring Break, school will resume on March 23, 2020. Individuals returning from travel to China, South Korea, Italy, Iran, Japan, or any other Level 2 or 3 country as identified by the CDC must quarantine for a period of 14 days before returning to school. This applies to all students, teachers, and other school or district staff. Please notify school administration if you traveled during Spring Break.

Thank you.

Henryetta Baseball
February 26 at 9:14 PM ·

H-Town. We want to give you an update about our program and what we have accomplished, as well as, what is coming up in the coming weeks. Our scoreboard has been completed and looks unbelievable! Again, we thank our sponsors, First National Bank and American Exchange. We also want to thank the numerous alumni that also generously donated. We want to thank the crew of alumni that took down the old scoreboard, ranging from Fighting Hens to recently graduated Knights (Dirtbags). We also want to give a huge thank you to the HPS maintenance department that installed our new scoreboard. Lastly, we thank Pullium Electric for hooking it up and getting it game ready. The blessings we have received from our Henryetta community is not taken for granted, and we thank you.

Our season opens March 2, at Lincoln Christian, with our home opener the following day March 3, at 4:30. We hope to see you there and throughout the season. #HTownProud

We want to thank the crew of alumni that took down the old scoreboard, ranging from Fighting Hens to recently graduated Knights (Dirtbags). We also want to give a huge thank you to the HPS maintenance department that installed our new scoreboard. Lastly, we thank Pullium Electric for hooking it up and getting it game ready. The blessings we have received from our Henryetta community is not taken for granted, and we thank you.

Our season opens March 2, at Lincoln Christian, with our home opener the following day March 3, at 4:30. We hope to see you there and throughout the season. #HTownProud

post_text:
Parent/Teacher Conferences will be Wed., Oct. 16 from 3:30 p.m. - 6:30 p.m. & Thurs., Oct. 17 from 9:00 a.m. - 12:00 p.m.

Our 1st annual College and Career Fair on Wed., Oct. 16th from 3:00 p.m. – 6:00 p.m. at the HS during Parent/Teacher conferences. Parents and students can learn more about college & career information, Oklahoma’s Promise, and FAFSA. Senior parents who claimed their senior student as a dependent on taxes last year may bring last year's tax information and receive assistance applying for FAFSA.

Fall Break will be on Thurs. (Oct. 17), Fri. (Oct. 18), and Mon. (Oct. 21). School will NOT be in session on those dates.

shared_text:
Henryetta FFA
October 1, 2019 at 8:02 PM ·

To say today was a fantastic day for us is a understatement. Tulsa State Fair Cattle Grading was a blast and our kids did so well! Out of 726 kids all of our kids placed in the upper half of them!
Ryan Clark was the top FFA individual
Jaxan Wright was 4th overall FFA individual
There were 225 teams and we had the top FFA team and the 15th as well! It’s a great day to be a Knight! #Htownproud

post_text:
Happy Game Day Friday, H-Town. Our 2019 Knight Football Team will open their season tonight vs. the Morris Eagles. Tonight’s game is on the road at Morris, and we are hoping to see you all there. H-Town Proud and H-Town Loud!

Kick-off is at 7:00 p.m., and we are asking for the safety of our football team and staff that students, parents, and community members not to enter the field during post-game. Players and coaches will return to the visiting side and may visit and celebrate before loading the bus.

Thank you for your help, cooperation, and understanding in this regard, and remember, “It’s Knight Time!”
